===Etymology===
From Old (and modern) French ''[[locuste]]'', from Latin ''[[locusta]]'' ‘locust, crustacean’.  Compare ''[[lobster]]''.

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/ˈləʊkəst/}}
*{{audio|en-us-locust.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# A type of [[grasshopper]] in the family [[Acrididae]] that flies in [[swarm]]s and is very [[destructive]] to [[crop]]s and other [[vegetation]].

